  <Content>Peasant Appreciation Day

Peasants are the most hard-working of Aislings.  Their toil gets the crops to market, keeps the mundane children and elderly in good health, and even provides for the furthering of alchemical research.  Each and every mighty master Aisling that walks the lands was at one point a humble peasant. The life of a peasant is full of toil.  Most seek an easier life.  However, on the 11th sun of the 5th moon of the 23rd Deoch, a peasant reached the highest of insights, proving that there are no heights to which a peasant cannot climb.  It is now the two cycle anniversary of this fateful day.  ����������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������In memorandum of this momentous achievement, peasants across the land are declaring the eightday of this anniversary ((Friday October 17th)) Peasant Appreciation Day.  Observe this holiday, if you will, by wearing once more the simple shirt or blouse you started your journey of light in, and celebrate the humble joys of peasant life as you will.
